docs.abstract: In a long speech to farmers on Monday, President Trump asked them to be patient and said his economic policies would pay off in the long-term.
docs.snippet: In a long speech to farmers on Monday, President Trump asked them to be patient and said his economic policies would pay off in the long-term.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, seeking to shore up his base of support in rural America, promised farmers on Monday that “the greatest harvest is yet to come” and insisted that the pain they were experiencing from his economic policies would ultimately make them better off.

headline.main: Trump Defends Trade Policies to Farmers Feeling the Pinch
headline.print_headline: It’ll Be Worth It, Trump Tells Farmers as His Policies Cause Them Pain

headline.main: After Heated Exchange, Matthew Whitaker Says He Will Testify Friday Before the House

docs.abstract: President Trump travels to El Paso today for a rally to win support for his call for a border wall. But this time, his potential rival in 2020, Beto O’Rourke, will be there to answer him.
docs.snippet: President Trump travels to El Paso today for a rally to win support for his call for a border wall. But this time, his potential rival in 2020, Beto O’Rourke, will be there to answer him.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s confrontations with potential Democratic challengers in 2020 have mostly been limited to sniping on Twitter. But on Monday night in El Paso, he will engage in his most direct conflict with a possible rival — former Representative Beto O’Rourke, a native of the city that shares a border with Mexico.

headline.main: Dueling Rallies in Texas for Trump and O’Rourke

docs.abstract: Lawmakers said they had reached the agreement after an impasse over the number of ICE detention beds had threatened to derail negotiations.
docs.snippet: Lawmakers said they had reached the agreement after an impasse over the number of ICE detention beds had threatened to derail negotiations.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House and Senate negotiators on Monday night agreed in principle to provide $1.375 billion for fencing and other physical barriers at the Mexican border, part of a broader agreement that would stave off another partial government shutdown without funding President Trump’s wall.

headline.main: With Shutdown Looming, Border Deal Is Reached ‘in Principle’
headline.print_headline: Deal ‘In Principle’ On Border Would Avoid a Shutdown

docs.abstract: Mr. Meacham, a Pulitzer Prize-winning author, and former President George Bush forged a deeply personal connection that was unusual for most historians and their subjects.
docs.snippet: Mr. Meacham, a Pulitzer Prize-winning author, and former President George Bush forged a deeply personal connection that was unusual for most historians and their subjects.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Around Labor Day in 1998, the historian Michael Beschloss took his friend, Jon Meacham, then a Newsweek writer, to Kennebunkport, Me., where Mr. Beschloss interviewed George Bush, the former president, at the family compound. After their conversation, Mr. Bush took both visitors on one of the hair-rising rides he loved to take on his speedboat.

headline.main: Jon Meacham, Bush’s Biographer, Will Also Deliver a Eulogy
headline.print_headline: A Biographer Who Forged A Personal Connection Will Also Deliver a Eulogy
